law.text: The Secretary of State, at the close of each session of the General Assembly, shall inspect the papers and documents which remain with the unfinished business, and carefully file in his office such as he considers worthy of preservation, with proper labels designating the session to which they belong.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 4544.
